# Bird Migration and Avian Flu

## Goal

Build a dashboard that helps the user explore whether there may be a relationship between bird migration and avian influenza outbreaks.

## Scope

The dashboard should focus on Europe.

## Main Features

The product should include an interactive map.

The map should show bird migration patterns over time.

For the first useful migration map, a coarser spatial grid is acceptable if it makes the data more readable and easier to process.

The map should also show avian influenza outbreak data.

The user should be able to move through time with a time slider.

## Time Resolution

For the first version, the smallest time unit should be one month.

## Migration Resolution

For the first practical eBird-based version, the migration layer may use a coarse grid of about `27 km` to `30 km` cells instead of the native `3 km` cells.

## Outbreak Data

For the first version, outbreak data should only include poultry cases.

